{"parse":{"title":"mushroom","pageid":36755,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"==English==\n{{wp}}\n{{picdic\n|image=Flammulina velutipes 04.jpg\n|detail1=\n{{picdicimg|en|image=AD2009Sep13 Boletus edulis 01.jpg|link=fungus}}\n|detail2=\n{{picdicimg|en|image=ChampignonMushroom.jpg|link=champignon}}\n{{picdicimg|en|image=Chanterelle Cantharellus cibarius.jpg|link=chanterelle}}\n{{picdicimg|en|image=Amanita muscaria 3 vliegenzwammen op rij.jpg|link=fly agaric}}\n{{picdicimg|en|image=Many-colored Polypore.jpg|link=polypore}}\n{{picdicimg|en|image=Steinpilz.jpg|link=porcini}}\n}}\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|muscheron}}, {{m|enm|musseron|}}, from {{der|en|xno|musherum}}, {{m|fro|moscheron}}, from {{der|en|fro|moisseron}}, of {{unk|en|title=obscure}} origin: probably derived from {{der|en|fro|mosse}}, {{m|fro|moise}} {{gl|\"moss\"; whence also {{m+|fr|mousse}}}}, as the use first applied to a type of fungus which grows in moss, from {{der|en|frk|*mosu|t=moss}} or {{der|en|odt|*mosa|t=moss}}, akin to {{cog|goh|mosa|t=moor, swamp}}, {{cog|goh|mos|t=moss, bog}}, {{cog|goh|mios|t=moss, mire}}, {{cog|ang|mēos|t=moss}}, {{cog|ang|mōs|t=bog, marsh}}, {{cog|non|mosi|t=moss}}, {{cog|non|myrr|t=bog, mire}}, from {{der|en|gem-pro|*musą}}, {{m|gem-pro|*musô}}, {{m|gem-pro|*miuziz|t=mosses, bog}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*mews-|t=mosses, mold, mildew}}. Displaced native {{ncog|ang|swamm}}. More at [[mire]]. Alternatively, the Old French may be of pre-Roman origin. See {{cog|grc|μύκης||mushroom}}. {{doublet|en|moss|mousse}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈmʌʃˌɹuːm/|/-ˌɹʊm/|/-ˌɹəm/|a=RP}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈmʌʃˌɹʉwm/|/-ˌɹɵm/|/-ˌɹəm/|a=SSB}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈmʊʃˌɹuːm/|/-ˌɹʊm/|/-ˌɹəm/|a=Northern England}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈmʌʃˌɾʉm/|/-ˌɾəm/|a=Scotland}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈmʌʃˌɹum/|/-ˌɹʊm/|/-ˌɹəm/|a=GA,CA}}\n** {{audio|en|en-us-mushroom.ogg|a=US}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈmɐʃˌɹʉːm/|/-ˌɹʊm/|/ˈ-ˌɹəm/|a=AU,NZ}}\n* {{hyphenation|en|mush|room}}\n* {{rhymes|en|ʌʃɹuːm|ʌʃɹʊm|s=2}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{en-noun}}\n\n# {{senseid|en|Q83093}} Any of the fleshy [[fruiting body|fruiting bodies]] of [[fungus|fungi]] typically produced above ground on soil or on their food sources (such as decaying wood).\n#: {{syn|en|shroom<qq:clipping>|mushrump<qq:obsolete>}}\n#: {{hyper|en|fruiting body|<|body}}\n#: {{hypo|en|toadstool<id:subset of Q83093>}}\n#: {{ux|en|Some '''mushrooms''' are edible whereas others are poisonous, and sometimes they are difficult to tell apart.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1961|author={{w|Harry E. Wedeck}}|title=Dictionary of Aphrodisiacs|publisher=The Citadel Press|location=New York|page=159|passage=Arabs consider the eating of '''mushrooms''' as an aphrodisiac aid.}}\n# {{senseid|en|fungus that produces Q83093}} A fungus producing such fruiting bodies.\n#: {{hyper|en|fungus<id:Q764>|<|organism<id:Q7239>}}\n#: {{cot|en|mold<id:Q159341>|yeast<id:Q45422>}}\n# [[champignon|Champignon]] or {{taxfmt|Agaricus bisporus|species}}, the mushroom species most commonly used in cooking.\n# Any of the mushroom-shaped [[peg]]s in [[bar billiards]].\n# {{lb|en|architecture}} A [[concrete]] [[column]] with a thickened portion at the top, used to support a [[slab]].\n# {{lb|en|obsolete|figurative}} One who rises suddenly from a low condition in life; an [[upstart]].\n#* {{RQ:Bacon Sylva Sylvarum|6|passage=upstarts {{...}}call in reproach '''mushrooms'''}}\n# {{lb|en|figurative}} Something that grows very quickly or seems to appear suddenly.\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1971|author=Gwen White|title=Antique Toys And Their Background|page=129|text=The craze [hula hoops] began in the U.S.A., and in October the boom crossed the Atlantic and 40 firms sprang into being, some being overnight '''mushrooms'''.}}\n# {{ellipsis of|en|mushroom cloud}}.\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|en\n| [[beefsteak mushroom]]s ({{taxlink|Fistulina hepatica|species}}; {{taxfmt|Gyromitra esculenta|species}})|[[brain mushroom]] ({{taxfmt|Gyromitra esculenta|species}})|[[button mushroom]] ({{taxfmt|Agaricus bisporus|species}})\n| [[Caesar's mushroom]] ({{taxfmt|Amanita caesarea|species}})|[[cauliflower mushroom]] ({{taxfmt|Sparassis|genus}} spp.)|[[chicken mushroom]]s ({{taxfmt|Laetiporus|genus}} spp.)|[[Chinese mushroom]] ({{taxfmt|Lentinula edodes|species}})\n| darning mushroom\n| [[enoki mushroom]] ({{taxlink|Flammulina filiformis|species}})\n| [[fairy ring mushroom]] ({{taxlink|Marasmius oreades|species}})|[[field mushroom]] ({{taxfmt|Agaricus campestris|species}})|[[fool's mushroom]] ({{taxlink|Amanita verna|species}})|[[fried chicken mushroom]] ({{taxlink|Lyophyllum decastes|species}})\n| [[gypsy mushroom]] ({{taxfmt|Cortinarius caperatus|species}})\n| [[honey mushroom]] ({{taxfmt|Armillaria|genus}} spp.)|[[horse mushroom]] ({{taxlink|Agaricus arvensis|species}})\n| king trumpet mushroom\n| little brown mushroom|[[little white mushroom]] ({{taxlink|Trogia venenata|species}})|{{vern|lobster mushroom}} ({{taxfmt|Hypomyces lactifluorum|species}})\n| [[magic mushroom]]|[[maize mushroom]] ({{taxlink|Mycosarcoma maydis|species}})|[[meadow mushroom]] ({{taxfmt|Agaricus campestris|species}})|mushie\n| mushroom anchor\n| mushroom body|mushroom brush|mushroomburger\n| mushroom cloud|[[mushroom coral]] ({{taxfmt|Fungiidae|family}} spp.)|mushroom cut\n| mushroomer\n| mushroom haircut|mushroom hat|mushroom head\n| mushroomic\n| mushroomless|mushroomlike,mushroom-like\n| mushroom millionaire\n| mushroomoid\n| mushroom party\n| [[mushroom root rot]] ({{taxlink|Armillaria tabescens|species}})\n| mushroom-shaped|mushroom spawn|mushroom stamp|mushroom syndrome\n| mushroom tip\n| mushroomy\n| [[oyster mushroom]] ({{taxfmt|Pleurotus|genus}} spp., {{taxfmt|Pleurotus ostreatus|species|P. ostreatus}})\n| [[parasol mushroom]] ({{taxfmt|Macrolepiota procera|species}})|psilocybin mushroom|psychedelic mushroom\n| [[St. George's mushroom]] ({{taxlink|Calocybe gambosa|species}})|[[Satan's mushroom]] ({{taxlink|Rubroboletus satanas|species}})|[[shoestring mushroom]] ({{taxfmt|Armillaria|genus}} spp.)|shrump|[[straw mushroom]] ({{taxlink|Volvariella volvacea|species}})\n| toothed jelly mushroom}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|ja|マッシュルーム|bor=1}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{multitrans|data=\n{{trans-top|fruiting body of a fungus}}\n* Acehnese: {{t-needed|ace}}\n* Afrikaans: {{tt+|af|sampioen}}\n* Ainu: {{t|ain|カルㇱ}}\n* Ahtna: {{t|aht|cʼeniyeʼ}}\n* Albanian: {{tt+|sq|kërpudhë|f}}\n* Altai:\n*: Northern Altai: {{tt|atv|пешке}}\n*: Southern Altai: {{tt|alt|мешке}}\n* Amharic: {{tt|am|እንጉዳይ}}\n* Arabic: {{tt+|ar|فُطْر|m}} {{tt|ar|عَيْش الْغُرَاب|m}}\n*: Egyptian Arabic: {{tt|arz|مشروم|m|tr=mašrōm, mašrūm}}, {{tt|arz|فطر|m|tr=feṭr}}, {{tt|arz|عيش الغراب|m|tr=ʕēš el-ḡorāb}}\n*: Gulf Arabic: {{tt|afb|مشروم|m}}, {{tt|afb|فطر|m}}\n*: Hijazi Arabic: {{tt|acw|فطر|m|tr=fiṭir}}\n*: Moroccan Arabic: {{tt|ary|شمپنيون|tr=šampinyūn}}\n* Aragonese: {{tt|an|potrecón}}, {{tt|an|fungo}}\n* Armenian: {{tt+|hy|սունկ}}\n* Aromanian: {{tt|rup|bureati|m}}, {{tt|rup|buburec}}\n* Assamese: {{tt|as|কাঠফুলা}}, {{tt|as|বেংছটা}}\n* Asturian: {{tt|ast|seta|f}}, {{tt|ast|cogorda|f}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{tt+|az|göbələk}}\n* Banjarese: {{tt|bjn|kulat}}\n* Bashkir: {{tt|ba|бәшмәк}}\n* Basque: {{tt|eu|perretxiko}}, {{tt|eu|ziza}}\n* Belarusian: {{tt|be|грыб|m}}\n* Bengali: {{tt+|bn|ছত্রাক}}\n* Bhojpuri: {{t|bho|कुकुरमुत्ता}}\n* Bikol:\n*: Central Bikol: {{tt|bcl|libgos}}\n* Bislama: {{tt|bi|sompiniong}}\n* Breton: {{tt+|br|kabell-touseg|m}}, {{tt+|br|boued-touseg|m}}\n* Bulgarian: {{tt+|bg|гъ́ба|f}}\n* Bunun: {{t|bnn|quung}}\n* Burmese: {{tt+|my|မှို}}\n* Buryat: {{tt|bua|мөөгэ}}, {{tt|bua|һархяаг}} {{qualifier|Russia}}\n* Catalan: {{tt+|ca|bolet|m}}, {{tt+|ca|fong|m}}\n* Cebuano: {{tt|ceb|uhong}}\n* Cham:\n*: Eastern Cham: {{tt|cjm|ꨝꨪꨯꨟꨱ|tr=bimau}}\n* Chamicuro: {{tt|ccc|kas̈hama}}\n* Chechen: {{tt|ce|жӏаьлин нускал}}\n* Cherokee: {{tt|chr|ᏓᏬᎵ}}\n* Chichewa: {{tt|ny|bowa}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Cantonese: {{tt|yue|蘑菇}}\n*: Dungan: {{tt|dng|могў}}\n*: Eastern Min: {{tt|cdo|菇}}, {{tt|cdo|菰|tr=gŭ}}, {{tt|cdo|蘑菇|tr=mò̤-gŭ