ллэй}}\n* Yiddish: {{tt|yi|שוואָם|m|f}}\n* Yoruba: {{tt|yo|olu}}, {{t|yo|osun}}\n* Zhuang: {{tt|za|yanghguh}}\n* Zulu: {{tt|zu|ikhowe}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|fungus itself}}\n* Bulgarian: {{tt+|bg|гъ́ба|f}}\n* Catalan: {{tt+|ca|bolet|m}}\n* Czech: {{tt+|cs|houba|f}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|sieni}}\n* Galician: {{tt+|gl|fungo|m}}\n* Georgian: {{tt|ka|სოკო}}\n* German: {{tt+|de|Pilz|m}}\n* Hungarian: {{tt+|hu|gomba}}\n* Irish: {{tt|ga|beacán|m}}, {{tt|ga|muisiriún|m}}\n* Kurdish:\n*: Northern Kurdish: {{tt+|kmr|karok}}\n* Manx: {{tt|gv|fliughane|m}}\n* Navajo: {{tt|nv|ábishjaaʼ}}\n* Pashto: {{tt+|ps|مرخېړی|m|tr=marxeṛay}}, {{tt|ps|غومبه|f|tr=ğumba}}\n* Plautdietsch: {{tt|pdt|Pilz|n}}\n* Polish: {{tt+|pl|grzyb|m}}\n* Portuguese: {{tt+|pt|fungo|m}}, {{tt+|pt|cogumelo|m}}\n* Russian: {{tt+|ru|грибни́ца|f}}\n* Slovene: {{tt+|sl|gliva|f}}\n* Swahili: {{tt+|sw|kuvu|c9|c10}}\n* Thai: {{tt+|th|เห็ด}}\n* Turkish: {{tt+|tr|mantar}}\n*: Ottoman Turkish: {{t|ota|مانطار|tr=mantar}}\n* Ukrainian: {{tt+|uk|гриб|m}}\n* Unami: {{t|unm|ahkokwe}}\n* Volapük: {{tt+|vo|funig}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-see|champignon}}\n\n{{trans-top|mushroom-shaped peg}}\n* Hungarian: {{tt+|hu|gomba}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-see|one who rises suddenly from a low condition in life|upstart}}\n\n{{trans-top|something that grows very quickly or seems to appear suddenly}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|pullataikina}} {{q|grows quickly}}; {{tt|fi|[[sienet]] [[sateella]]}} {{q|appear suddenly in large quantity}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{checktrans-top}}\n* Scottish Gaelic: {{tt-check|gd|balgan-buachair|m}}, {{tt-check|gd|balg-buachrach|m}}\n* Woiwurrung: {{t-check|wyi|bik-gurn}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n}}\n\n====See also====\n{{col|en\n|cep,cepe,cèpe\n|champignon\n|chanterelle\n|cremini\n|fungus\n|morel\n|porcino\n|{{l|en|portabela}}<!--AHD-->, [[portabella]]<!--OED-->, [[portabello]]<!--OED, Barron's-->, [[portobela]]<!--AHD-->, [[portobella]]<!--Barron's-->, [[portobello]]<!--OED, Barron's-->, [[portobelo]]<!--AHD-->\n|shiitake\n|toadstool\n}}\n\n====Further reading====\n{{R:Lexico}}\n\n===Adjective===\n{{en-adj|-}}\n\n# {{lb|en|attributive}} Having characteristics like those of a [[#Noun|mushroom]], for example in shape or appearance, speed of growth, or texture.\n#: {{ux|en|[[mushroom cloud|'''mushroom''' cloud]]}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{multitrans|data=\n{{trans-top|resembling a mushroom}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|sienimäinen}}, {{tt+|fi|sieni|alt=sieni-}}\n* Hungarian: {{tt+|hu|gomba}}\n* Irish: {{tt|ga|muisiriúnach}}\n* Macedonian: {{tt|mk|печуркаст|m}}\n* Portuguese: {{tt|pt|([[em]] [[forma]]) [[de]] [[cogumelo]]}}\n* Russian: {{tt+|ru|грибови́дный}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{en-verb}}\n\n# {{lb|en|intransitive|figurative}} To grow [[quickly]] to a large size or rapidly increase in scope or scale.\n#: {{ux|en|The town’s population '''mushroomed''' from 10,000 to 110,000 in five years.}}\n#* {{quote-book\n|en\n|year=2009\n|author=Zhang Yulin\n|chapter=China's War on its Environment and Farmers' Rights: A Study of Shanxi Province\n|title=Confronting Discrimination and Inequality in China: Chinese and Canadian Perspectives\n|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=nX-sDAAAQBAJ\n|publisher=w:University of Ottawa Press\n|ISBN=978-0-7766-0709-2\n|OCLC=302060940\n|page=166\n|pageurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=nX-sDAAAQBAJ&pg=PA166\n|text=In Beilu Village<!--北劉村--> of Liucun Town<!--劉村鎮--> in Yaodu District,<!--堯都區--> Linfen,<!--臨汾市--> abnormal illnesses continued to emerge, as a result of clusters of highly-polluting enterprises '''mushrooming''' in the vicinity.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|author=w:Oliver Wainwright|title=Super-tall, super-skinny, super-expensive: the ‘pencil towers’ of New York’s super-rich|editor=w:Katharine Viner|newspaper=w:The Guardian|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20201005122034/https://www.theguardian.com/cities/2019/feb/05/super-tall-super-skinny-super-expensive-the-pencil-towers-of-new-yorks-super-rich|archivedate=5 October 2020|location=London|publisher=[[w:Guardian Media Group|Guardian News & Media]]|date=1 June 2019|issn=0261-3077|oclc=229952407|passage=The world's population of ultra-high-net-worth individuals, a super-elite with assets of at least $30m, has now '''mushroomed''' beyond 250,000 people, all in need of somewhere to store their wealth.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|author=Thomas L. Friedman|title=Cyberspace Plus Trump Almost Killed Our Democracy. Can Europe Save Us?|work=The New York Times|date=2021-02-10|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2021/02/09/opinion/cyberspace-democracy-europe.html|issn=0362-4331|passage=It has its own global news gathering and sharing platforms, like Facebook, YouTube and Twitter. {{...}} In recent years, all these platforms have '''mushroomed'''.}}\n# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To [[gather]] [[#Noun|mushroom]]s.\n#: {{ux|en|We used to go '''mushrooming''' in the forest every weekend.}}\n# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To form the shape of a [[#Noun|mushroom]].\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=2001|author=James E. Duffy|title=I-Car Professional Automotive Collision Repair|page=173\n|passage=Excessive spot weld time may cause the electrode tips to '''mushroom''', resulting in no focus of current and a weak weld.}}\n## {{lb|en|ballistics|of a [[bullet#Noun|bullet]]}} To form the shape of a [[#Noun|mushroom]] when striking a [[soft]] [[target]].\n\n====Translations====\n{{multitrans|data=\n{{trans-top|to grow quickly}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{tt|az|yağışdan sonra göbələk kimi çıxmaq}}\n* Bulgarian: {{tt|bg|раста бързо}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|paisua}}\n* French: {{tt+|fr|champignonner}}\n* German: {{tt+|de|wuchern}}\n* Hungarian: {{tt|hu|[[gomba]] [[módra]] / [[gombamód]] [[szaporodik]]}}, {{tt|hu|[[gyorsan]] [[növekszik]]}}\n* Polish: {{tt+|pl|rosnąć jak grzyby po deszczu|impf}}, {{tt+|pl|rosnąć jak na drożdżach|impf}}\n* Portuguese: {{tt+|pt|estourar}}, {{tt+|pt|explodir}}\n* Swedish: {{tt+|sv|explodera}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|to gather mushrooms}}\n* Bulgarian: {{tt|bg|бера гъби}}\n* Czech: {{tt|cs|houbařit}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|sienestää}}\n* French: {{tt+|fr|champignonner}}\n* Galician: {{tt+|gl|apañar|alt=apañar cogomelos}}, {{tt+|gl|coller|alt=coller cogomelos}}\n* German: {{tt|de|Pilze ernten}}, {{tt|de|Pilze sammeln}}\n* Hungarian: {{tt+|hu|gombászik}}, {{tt+|hu|gombázik}}\n* Irish: {{tt|ga|bheith ag baint muisiriún}}, {{tt|ga|bheith ag baint beacán}}\n* Latvian: {{t+|lv|sēņot}}\n* Lithuanian: {{tt|lt|grybauti}}\n* Macedonian: {{tt|mk|печуркари}}\n* Portuguese: {{tt|pt|[[colher]] [[cogumelos]]}}\n* Swedish: {{tt|sv|plocka svamp}}\n* Turkish: {{t|tr|mantar toplamak}}\n* Turkmen: {{t|tk|kömelek çöplemek}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n}}\n\n{{C|en|Mushrooms|People}}"}}